[2/16]

Who are you and what are your goals?

R and Python are both great languages, but they have strengths and weaknesses.

#data #datascience #rstats #Python #dataanalytics

Having said that, I personally consider R (and specifically, The Tidyverse) to be a better *analytics* language.

#Python #rstats #datascience #dataanalytics

[4/16]

At a high level:

Python is a better general purpose language, and a better machine learning language.

R is a better data analytics language.

#data #datascience #rstats #Python #dataanalytics https://t.co/Y7lILP2ZIR

[15/16]

In the end, you may want to learn both R *and* Python ...

But that's going to be hard to do.

And if you're just getting started with data science I recommend focusing on one language.

#rstats #python #datascience

[16/16]

Do you have questions about R vs Python for data science?

If so, leave a comment and I'll reply.

#datascience #rstats #python #dataanalytics #machinelearning

"Which language should I learn for data science, R or Python?"

This is a common question I get from data science beginners.

My answer to this question is almost always: "It depends"

🧵[1/16]

#data #datascience #rstats #Python #dataanalytics https://t.co/YzaReOYi8T

[5/16]

And to clarify:

When I say that I like "R" for data analytics ...

What I really mean is the *Tidyverse* dialect of R, which includes ggplot2, dplyr, tidyr, stringr, etc.

#data #datascience #rstats #dataanalytics

One of the advantages of Python over R is that Python is often considered a better "general purpose" language.

https://t.co/WqPwTFofAd

#Python #rstats #programming #datascience https://t.co/y1V8ytQXTe

[3/16]

The language that you choose depends on your goals ...

It depends on what you're trying to do and who you're trying to become.

#data #datascience #rstats #Python #dataanalytics

[9/16]

For machine learning R has been less developed until recently, although there have been some recent additions to The Tidyverse for ML and model building.

#DataScience  #rstats #machinelearning

[8/16]

R is less good as a "general purpose" language, because a lot of the traditional syntax from "Base R" feels clumsy.

If I need to do anything that feels more like software creation, I avoid R.

#datascience #programming #rstats

[14/16]

If you want to be a hardcore data analyst, then I'd definitely recommend R.

#rstats #datascience #dataanalytics

[7/16]

For data wrangling, data visualization, and data analysis ...

R is a dream to use.

Really.  I love using it.

#data #datascience #rstats #dataanalytics

[6/16]

So generally, R is a better data analytics language.

Any time I need to analyze data ... including getting, wrangling, visualizing, aggregating, and summarizing data ...

R is my preferred language.

#data #datascience #rstats #dataanalytics
